  "text": "Moexipril can be determined using both gas chromatography (GC) (4) and high-performance liquid chromatography (HPLC) [CITATION_1] . The GC analysis (4) consists of several steps, such as: (a) clean-up using Bond Elute C18, (b) methylation, (c) acid-base partition, and (d) converting both moexipril and moexiprilat to the corresponding trifluoroacetamides. GC separation can be monitored using negative-ion chemical ionization (NICI) mass spectrometry (MS) for the fragment ions of m/z 302 and 288 for moexipril and moexiprilat, respectively. The use of GC has been limited by the requirement of two-steps derivatization, that is, methylation and trifluoroacetylation.",
